            <h2>About Me</h2>
            <p>Every year, many individuals, including kids
under the age of 5 drown in the deeps of the swimming pool,
and the lifeguards are not well trained enough to handle these
situations. Thus arises the requirement for having a system
that will consequently detect the drowning individuals and
alarm the life guard at such risk. Swimming pool surveillance
systems plays an essential role in safeguarding the premises. In
this project differential pressure approach is used for detection
of drowning incidents in swimming pools at the earliest
possible stage.The Virtual Eye software works in close integration with the cameras installed in the pool to continuously scan the pool. 
            </p>
